## `test_dir_nlink_counts_subdirs(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-nodes-20 -->

### Purpose
POSIX `nlink` on a directory equals 2 + number of direct subdirectory children (one each for `.` from every subdir, plus `.` and the parent's entry for itself). Files don't add to the parent's `nlink`.

### Postconditions

```python
# Empty dir: nlink == 2
as_root.mkdir("/a")
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 2

# Add two subdirs: nlink == 4
as_root.mkdir("/a/sub1")
as_root.mkdir("/a/sub2")
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 4

# Add a regular file: nlink on /a unchanged
fd = as_root.create("/a/file")
as_root.close_fd(fd)
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 4

# Remove one subdir: nlink == 3
as_root.rmdir("/a/sub1")
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 3
```

---

## `test_unique_parent_name_constraint(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-nodes-21 -->

### Purpose
A file and a directory cannot share a name under the same parent. The UNIQUE(parent, name) SQL constraint is enforced at the schema level; the library maps the violation to `AlreadyExists`.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/x")
as_root.close_fd(fd)
with pytest.raises(AlreadyExists):
    as_root.mkdir("/x")
```

---

## `test_inodes_are_unique_and_stable(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-nodes-22 -->

### Purpose
Every node receives a unique inode number. Inode numbers do not change across close/reopen (invariant #6 from idea.md).

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.mkdir("/a")
fd = as_root.create("/b")
as_root.close_fd(fd)

inode_a = as_root.stat("/a").inode
inode_b = as_root.stat("/b").inode
inode_root = as_root.stat("/").inode

assert inode_root == 1
assert inode_a != inode_b != inode_root
assert inode_a > 1 and inode_b > 1
```

